    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Rinse your<strong> brown rice</strong>, add it to a pot with plenty of <strong>cold water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium and cook for 20-25 min or until it's tender with a slight bite</p><p>Once cooked, drain, return it to the pot and keep covered until serving</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/crispy-tofu-with-sesame-rice-and-satay-sauce-with-brown-rice/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, boil half a kettle</p><p>Drain your<strong> tofu</strong>, then pat it dry with kitchen paper</p><p>Cut the <strong>tofu</strong> into 6<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span>strips per person</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/crispy-tofu-with-sesame-rice-and-satay-sauce-with-brown-rice/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a generous drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a high heat</p><p>Once very hot, add the <strong>tofu strips</strong> and cook for 5-6 min, turning occasionally until golden and crisp</p><p>Once the tofu is crisp, transfer it to kitchen paper and set aside (reserve the pan for later!) \u2013 this is your <strong>crispy tofu</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/crispy-tofu-with-sesame-rice-and-satay-sauce-with-brown-rice/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the tofu is cooking, chop your <strong>creamed coconut</strong> roughly (if required!)</p><p>Dissolve the <strong>chopped creamed</strong> <strong>coconut</strong>, your <strong>peanut butter</strong>, <strong>red chilli relish</strong> and <strong>soy sauce </strong>in 200ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[300ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[400ml]</span><strong> boiled water </strong>in a jug</p><p>Stir it all together \u2013 this is your <strong>peanut stock</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/crispy-tofu-with-sesame-rice-and-satay-sauce-with-brown-rice/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Peel lengths off your <strong>cucumber</strong> until you end up with a pile of cucumber ribbons, discard the watery seeds</p><p>Add the<strong> cucumber ribbons</strong> to a large bowl and set aside</p><p>Add your <strong>rice vinegar</strong> to the cucumber<strong> </strong>ribbons and season with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> \u2013 this is your <strong>cucumber salad</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/crispy-tofu-with-sesame-rice-and-satay-sauce-with-brown-rice/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Carefully wipe the reserved pan clean and return it to a medium-low heat</p><p>Add the <strong>peanut stock</strong> to the pan and cook for 2-4 min or until thickened slightly \u2013 this is your <strong>satay sauce</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/crispy-tofu-with-sesame-rice-and-satay-sauce-with-brown-rice/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Fluff the <strong>cooked rice</strong> with a fork, add your <strong>black sesame seeds </strong>and give everything a good mix up \u2013 this is your <strong>sesame rice</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/crispy-tofu-with-sesame-rice-and-satay-sauce-with-brown-rice/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>crispy tofu</strong> over the <strong>sesame rice</strong> with the <strong>cucumber salad</strong> to the side</p><p>Pour the<strong> satay sauce</strong> all over the<strong> </strong>crispy tofu</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
